cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the quality of community structure in networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a modification to an existing metric. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the limitations of an algorithmic approach (modularity maximization) and proposes a new metric. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as community detection is a common task in machine learning. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the structure of networks.
